<br>
Thus, my spec at 50 will be 45 Savagery, 48 HTH, x Parry (whatever is left over).  This, in the end, maximizes my WeapSkill after getting myself the 25% Evade buff.<br>
<br>
But, by no means is this the ultimate Savage spec.  It's just the one I prefer based on my play styles and wants. <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.ameritech.net/users/trevanti/savagebanner5.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#ffffff><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zentrias>Zentrias</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Initiate</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#000000>(2/20/03 7:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=17.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Spec for a savage?</span><hr size=1> I assume that if Savages had all 3 damage types available it would've been seen as &quot;unbalanced.&quot; Nobody else in Midgaard could use either a pierce, slash, or bludgeon type of attack off the same weapon skill...<br>
<br>
I think. Been cancelled a long time, recently bought SI again...kobold warrior rocked, but I sure do laugh when I see my Tall troll hand-to-hand meleeing creatures. (Something I always wanted to see. If only they had caved in put in horned helmets! I signed a petition for those many months back) <br>
<br>
I dunno. Savagery looks pretty lame imho(good way to get yourself killed sucking the health out of you for those short buffs.) I'm dropping extra points into parry to get the straight % increase so I won't have to worry about cannibilizing myself to get 30 seconds of enhanced dodging...but then again, like I said, only recently returned to DAoC. and my savage isn't even into thidranki level yet =) <p>&lt;img src=&quot;http://vomitpopsicle.com/dumbstuff/jesuslove/lovah.JPG&quot; border=0&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://vomitpopsicle.com/dumbstuff/jesuslove/index.html&quot; target=&quot;black&quot;&gt;<br>
